# Docker Verification Protocol

After completing implementation work on any branch, browser-based UI verification is **MANDATORY** before marking work as complete or creating a PR.

## Docker Build & Run

1. Build from the worktree/branch being tested (not from a pre-built image):
   ```bash
   cd <worktree-path> && docker build -t agent-zero-test .
   ```

2. Run with the **same volume mount** as the real deployment (`docker/run/docker-compose.yml`):
   ```bash
   docker run -d --name a0-test \
     -v <worktree-path>:/a0 \
     -p 50081:80 \
     agent-zero-test
   ```

   The entire project dir is mounted as `/a0`. This preserves:
   - `usr/.env` — API keys and environment config
   - `usr/settings.json` — runtime settings
   - `usr/cognee/` — Cognee knowledge/data storage
   - All plugins, extensions, prompts

   For worktree testing, copy `usr/` from the main repo into the worktree before running:
   ```bash
   cp -r /path/to/agent-zero/usr <worktree-path>/usr
   ```
   Or symlink it: `ln -s /path/to/agent-zero/usr <worktree-path>/usr`

3. Wait for full startup (preload of ML models can take 1-2 minutes).

## Browser Verification Checklist

Open `http://localhost:50081` in the browser and verify:

- [ ] Login page loads (if auth enabled) or main UI loads
- [ ] Plugin list visible in settings (all 16 plugins discovered)
- [ ] Settings page opens without errors
- [ ] Chat input works (type and send a message)
- [ ] Agent responds (if API keys configured)
- [ ] Memory save: send a message that triggers memorization (e.g. "remember that X is Y")
- [ ] Memory recall: in a new chat, ask the agent to recall the saved fact — confirms the full memory pipeline (save + Cognee + recall)
- [ ] Any feature-specific UI related to the current branch changes

## Docker Logs Check

After browser testing, always check logs for errors:
```bash
docker logs a0-test 2>&1 | grep -i "error\|traceback\|exception" | grep -v "INFO\|DEBUG\|deprecation"
```

## Cleanup

```bash
docker stop a0-test && docker rm a0-test
```

## Key Paths

- Docker compose: `docker/run/docker-compose.yml`
- Dockerfile: `Dockerfile` (root)
- Runtime state: `usr/.env`, `usr/settings.json`, `usr/cognee/`
- Port: 50080 (production), 50081 (testing)
